  "response": "Google shut down its URL shortening service, goo.gl, on **March 30, 2019 for most users**. Existing shortened links created before that date were supposed to continue to redirect to their destinations \"for the foreseeable future.\"\n\nHowever, there have been reports of some older goo.gl links no longer working. While Google hasn't announced an end date for the redirection service, it is clear that they are not actively maintaining it and its reliability may degrade over time.\n\n**In summary:**\n\n*   **No guarantee:** While Google intended for goo.gl links to continue working indefinitely, there is no guarantee that they will.\n*   **Use alternatives:** It's highly recommended to use a different URL shortening service for any new links you create.\n*   **Possible expiration:** Be aware that older goo.gl links may stop working at some point in the future.\n*   **No official end-of-life date:** Google has not announced an official date for when the redirection service will be completely discontinued.\n",
